history.content: 188 and 186 have similar workload I think. Either course is "useful" if you are interested in AI or databases. Taking 188 doesn't immediately lead you to industries but with knowledge from 186, you can do a lot of stuff I assume. I haven't taken 134 but my friends said depending on the professor it could go really nasty in the end. Don't quote me thou. I think while CS170 is like a "must", take some classes that interest you. For example, I probably won't take 186 just for the sake of internship.

children.subject: Thats why I put a quote on must just because it helps a lot to understand the algorithm part in many other classes like 188.

I'm from the EE side but from many of my friends who are doing very well in securing CS internship and full-time positions, the 2 most important classes for "getting an internship" are 61b and 170 since a lot of interview questions are related to them. Just providing an opinion based on my own experience.

170 is a must if you wish to develop your algorithmic thinking skills, since that's what'll help you most in your career, even in industry; you can pick up databases and networks and OS on your own, but algorithm design skills can only be developed through practice.
CS170 is definitely not a "must". To me, it is just a totally pointless class.
